{"article_id":"NSf2xoExRcg2qpCy","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"SWAN QUARTER , N.C. -","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"Florence showed no sign","depth":10},{"id":2,"text":"of letting up Saturday ,","depth":10},{"id":3,"text":"taking its torrential rain , powerful winds and storm surges deep into South Carolina before an expected northerly turn","depth":10},{"id":4,"text":"that could head it toward the Ohio Valley ,","depth":10},{"id":5,"text":"the National Hurricane Center reported .","depth":8},{"id":6,"text":"Since marching ashore Friday near Wilmington , North Carolina , as a hurricane ,","depth":9},{"id":7,"text":"Florence had claimed five lives ,","depth":10},{"id":8,"text":"caused widespread flooding","depth":11},{"id":9,"text":"and knocked out power to nearly 900,000 homes .","depth":11},{"id":10,"text":"Now , as a tropical storm , it is expected to produce more flash floods","depth":10},{"id":11,"text":"as it drops up to another 25 inches of rain in some areas .","depth":10},{"id":12,"text":"Also possible are storm surges of up to 7 feet and possible tornadoes .","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"At 2 a.m. EST Saturday , the center of the storm was about 35 miles from Myrtle Beach , South Carolina , with maximum sustained winds at 50 mph .","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"It was moving at a paltry 5 mph .","depth":7},{"id":15,"text":"In the first report of storm-related fatalities , a mother and infant died","depth":11},{"id":16,"text":"after a tree fell on a house in Wilmington , North Carolina ,","depth":11},{"id":17,"text":"according to local police .","depth":10},{"id":18,"text":"The father was hospitalized with injuries .","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"In addition , a woman in Hampstead suffered a heart attack Friday morning ,","depth":10},{"id":20,"text":"but emergency crews","depth":13},{"id":21,"text":"hampered by downed trees in the road","depth":13},{"id":22,"text":"could not reach her","depth":12},{"id":23,"text":"before she died ,","depth":11},{"id":24,"text":"ABC News reports .","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"A fourth person was killed","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"while plugging in a generator","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"and a fifth","depth":10},{"id":28,"text":"when he was blown down","depth":11},{"id":29,"text":"trying to check on his hunting dogs in Lenoir County , north of Wilmington ,","depth":11},{"id":30,"text":"said Emergency Planner Samuel Kornegay , emergency planner for the county 's emergency services division .","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"North Carolina Gov . Roy Cooper said Friday","depth":9},{"id":32,"text":"that several other deaths were under investigation","depth":10},{"id":33,"text":"as possibly related to the storm .","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"`` We have days of rain ahead of us , ''","depth":11},{"id":35,"text":"he warned .","depth":11},{"id":36,"text":"`` If you 're asked to evacuate ,","depth":11},{"id":37,"text":"go . ''","depth":11},{"id":38,"text":"Meteorologist Ryan Maue of weathermodels.com calculates","depth":11},{"id":39,"text":"that Hurricane Florence is forecast to dump 9.6 trillion gallons , enough rain","depth":12},{"id":40,"text":"to cover the Tar Heel state in about 10 inches of water .","depth":12},{"id":41,"text":"The National Weather Service says","depth":11},{"id":42,"text":"16 inches of rain has already fallen in parts of North Carolina .","depth":11},{"id":43,"text":"Tom Collins , emergency management director in Pender County , N.C. , says","depth":9},{"id":44,"text":"the woman in Hampstead had a heart attack Friday morning ,","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"but emergency crews could not get to her","depth":11},{"id":46,"text":"because of the downed trees .","depth":11},{"id":47,"text":"Collins says","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"crews have a front loader","depth":11},{"id":49,"text":"they 're using","depth":12},{"id":50,"text":"to clear roads ,","depth":12},{"id":51,"text":"but a tree went through the windshield .","depth":10},{"id":52,"text":"In New Bern ,","depth":13},{"id":53,"text":"where the Neuse and Trent rivers intersect ,","depth":13},{"id":54,"text":"around 200 people were rescued","depth":12},{"id":55,"text":"after being stranded in their homes overnight ,","depth":11},{"id":56,"text":"according to Mayor Dana Outlaw .","depth":10},{"id":57,"text":"Another 150 ,","depth":11},{"id":58,"text":"including some trapped in second floors of houses or in attics ,","depth":11},{"id":59,"text":"awaited rescue .","depth":10},{"id":60,"text":"`` What happens is that we rescue some people","depth":10},{"id":61,"text":"and then we find out","depth":11},{"id":62,"text":"there are still more","depth":12},{"id":63,"text":"who need it , ''","depth":12},{"id":64,"text":"Outlaw said .","depth":9},{"id":65,"text":"`` People","depth":10},{"id":66,"text":"who live in New Bern","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"have experienced hurricanes before ,","depth":9},{"id":68,"text":"but it has been a long time","depth":9},{"id":69,"text":"since we have experienced something like this . ''","depth":9},{"id":70,"text":"The mayor said","depth":8},{"id":71,"text":"at least 4,200 homes and 300 businesses sustained damage from flooding .","depth":8},{"id":72,"text":"`` Things here are very , very serious , ''","depth":9},{"id":73,"text":"he said .","depth":9},{"id":74,"text":"`` If you 've ever doubted the destructiveness of a hurricane ,","depth":9},{"id":75,"text":"what 's happening here will make you a believer . ''","depth":9},{"id":76,"text":"Authorities advised residents","depth":10},{"id":77,"text":"who have not evacuated","depth":10},{"id":78,"text":"to go to the highest point in their homes ,","depth":9},{"id":79,"text":"call 911 for help ,","depth":9},{"id":80,"text":"keep their cell batteries charged","depth":11},{"id":81,"text":"as best they can","depth":11},{"id":82,"text":"and wait for help to arrive .","depth":10},{"id":83,"text":"More than 60 people ,","depth":12},{"id":84,"text":"including an infant , children and their pets ,","depth":12},{"id":85,"text":"were rescued from a collapsing hotel in Jacksonville , North Carolina , at the height of the storm ,","depth":11},{"id":86,"text":"according to WITN-TV .","depth":10},{"id":87,"text":"Cinder blocks","depth":13},{"id":88,"text":"that were part of the structure","depth":13},{"id":89,"text":"crumbled in some places","depth":12},{"id":90,"text":"and portions of the roof were missing .","depth":11},{"id":91,"text":"Police and fire teams forced their way into some rooms","depth":11},{"id":92,"text":"to free the residents ,","depth":12},{"id":93,"text":"who were temporarily taken to the town 's center for public safety .","depth":12},{"id":94,"text":"Rescuers were able to reach a flooded animal shelter in Newport , N.C. ,","depth":11},{"id":95,"text":"after the Carteret County Humane Society put out a call for help on Facebook .","depth":11},{"id":96,"text":"The Cajun Navy , a group of volunteers in boats , brought two stranded shelter workers , 43 dogs , 80 cats and roughly 15 chickens to safety .","depth":10},{"id":97,"text":"About 9,700 National Guard troops and civilians have been deployed , with high-water vehicles , helicopters and boats .","depth":9},{"id":98,"text":"`` I see a biblical proportion flood event","depth":11},{"id":99,"text":"that 's going to occur , ''","depth":11},{"id":100,"text":"Wilmington Police Chief Ralph Evangelous told ABC News .","depth":10},{"id":101,"text":"`` I see the beach communities being inundated with water and destruction","depth":10},{"id":102,"text":"that will be pretty , pretty epic in nature . ''","depth":10},{"id":103,"text":"Some 908,614 customers were without power in the Carolinas early Saturday ,","depth":9},{"id":104,"text":"according to poweroutage.us .","depth":9},{"id":105,"text":"National Weather Service forecasters said","depth":12},{"id":106,"text":"the storm would roam along the coast for at least two more days","depth":13},{"id":107,"text":"before reaching Columbia , South Carolina , early Sunday .","depth":13},{"id":108,"text":"It was also expected to slip briefly back into the open water during the journey .","depth":11},{"id":109,"text":"`` This storm will be a marathon vs. a sprint , ''","depth":12},{"id":110,"text":"the National Weather Service said on Twitter .","depth":12},{"id":111,"text":"`` In addition to the ongoing , dangerous storm surge and flash flooding , will be a long-term river flood threat WELL INLAND","depth":12},{"id":112,"text":"as very heavy rainfall continues to fall in the coming days . '' '","depth":12},{"id":113,"text":"The NHC said","depth":11},{"id":114,"text":"Florence went ashore near Wrightsville Beach , North Carolina , at 7:15 a.m. EDT with estimated maximum winds of 90 mph .","depth":11},{"id":115,"text":"Shortly afterward , the National Weather Service reported wind gusts to 105 mph at Wilmington International Airport , the highest wind gust","depth":12},{"id":116,"text":"measured in Wilmington","depth":13},{"id":117,"text":"since Hurricane Helene hit the port city in 1958 .","depth":13},{"id":118,"text":"The center said","depth":12},{"id":119,"text":"the water level could hit from 7 to 10 feet from Cape Fear to Cape Lookout , North Carolina , and from 6 to 9 feet from Cape Lookout to Ocracoke Inlet .","depth":12},{"id":120,"text":"Even with the storm raging ,","depth":10},{"id":121,"text":"the Army Corps of Engineers prepared to start work","depth":11},{"id":122,"text":"to restore power ,","depth":12},{"id":123,"text":"install temporary roofing","depth":13},{"id":124,"text":"and remove debris .","depth":13},{"id":125,"text":"While thousands chose to flee the coast ,","depth":11},{"id":126,"text":"others hunkered down .","depth":11},{"id":127,"text":"Gigi Charlebois , owner of the Edenton Coffee House on the northern shore of North Carolina 's Albemarle Sound , decided to stay with her family overnight in the shop 's dining room ,","depth":14},{"id":128,"text":"sleeping on couches , pull-out cots and a mattress .","depth":14},{"id":129,"text":"She said","depth":14},{"id":130,"text":"the shop , with an electric generator , was safer than their nearby home .","depth":14},{"id":131,"text":"\" It ' s unsafe , a lot of trees , \"","depth":14},{"id":132,"text":"Charlebois said .","depth":14},{"id":133,"text":"\" So ,","depth":14},{"id":134,"text":"even if it was just a tropical storm","depth":16},{"id":135,"text":"and trees went down","depth":16},{"id":136,"text":"we ' d have a hard time","depth":16},{"id":137,"text":"getting here . \"","depth":16},{"id":138,"text":"Staying there also allowed her to keep an eye on their freezers and fridges","depth":13},{"id":139,"text":"holding food .","depth":13},{"id":140,"text":"Plus , they ' d be there in the morning","depth":14},{"id":141,"text":"if first responders needed them .","depth":14},{"id":142,"text":"\" That ' s why we opened an hour later ,","depth":15},{"id":143,"text":"because we had to clean up all our bedding , \"","depth":15},{"id":144,"text":"Charlebois said","depth":15},{"id":145,"text":"while standing in the dining room ,","depth":16},{"id":146,"text":"which by Friday morning teemed with customers","depth":17},{"id":147,"text":"while rain poured outside .","depth":17},{"id":148,"text":"More :","depth":5},{"id":149,"text":"Waiting for Florence :","depth":6},{"id":150,"text":"Tales from the front lines of an approaching hurricane","depth":6},{"id":151,"text":"The National Hurricane Center said","depth":5},{"id":152,"text":"the storm would move further inland across extreme southeastern North Carolina and extreme eastern South Carolina on Friday and Saturday .","depth":6},{"id":153,"text":"Florence will then move generally northward across the western Carolinas and the central Appalachian Mountains early next week .","depth":6},{"id":154,"text":"Contributing :","depth":3},{"id":155,"text":"The Associated Press ; Joey Gill ; Katie Wadington ; Chris Woodyard and Sean Rossman","depth":3}],"relations":[{"parent":311,"left":0,"right":310,"relation":"organization",